obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (35778)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35778&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Dalmia Dadri Cement Limited`
  line `(Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1981.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 23rd day of June, 1981.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (35779)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35779&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the 23rd day of June, 1981;`
  line
  line `(b) "Cement Corporation" means the Cement Corporation of India, a company incorporated and`
  line `registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(c) "Commissioner" means the Commissioner of Payments appointed under section 14;`
  line
  line `(d) "Company" means the Dalmia Dadri Cement Limited, being a company within the meaning`
  line `of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), and having its registered office at Charkhi Dadri (Haryana);`
  line
  line `(e) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "specified date", in relation to any provision of this Act, means such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify for the purposes of that provision, and different dates may`
  line `be specified for different provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), shall have the meanings, respectively, assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (35780)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government of the undertakings of the Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35780&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On the appointed day, the undertakings of the Company, and the right, title and interest of`
  line `the Company in relation to its undertakings, shall, by virtue of this Act, stand transferred to, and vest in,`
  line `the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (35781)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `General effect of vesting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35781&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The undertakings of the Company shall be deemed to include all`
  line `assets, rights, lease-holds, powers, authorities and privileges, and all property, movable and immovable,`
  line `including lands, buildings, workshops, stores, instruments, machinery and equipment, cash balances, cash`
  line `on hand, reserve funds, investments, book debts and all other rights and interests in, or arising out of, such`
  line `property as were immediately before the appointed day in the ownership, possession, power or control of`
  line `the Company, whether within or outside India, and all books of account, registers and all other documents`
  line `of whatever nature relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) All properties as aforesaid which have vested in the Central Government under section 3 shall, by`
  line `force of such vesting, be freed and discharged from any trust, obligation, mortgage, charge, lien and all`
  line `other incumbrances affecting them, and any attachment, injunction, decree or order of any court`
  line `restricting the use of such properties in any manner shall be deemed to have been withdrawn.`
  line
  line `(3) Every mortgagee of any property which has vested under this Act in the Central Government and`
  line `every person holding any charge, lien or other interest in, or in relation to, any such property, shall give,`
  line `within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, an intimation to the Commissioner of such`
  line `mortgage, charge, lien or other interest.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the mortgagee of any property referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) or any other person holding any charge, lien or other interest in, or in relation to, any such`
  line `property shall be entitled to claim, in accordance with his rights and interests, payment of the mortgage`
  line `money or other dues, in whole or in part, out of the amount specified in section 7 and also out of the`
  line `amount determined under section 8, but no such mortgage, charge, lien or other interest shall be`
  line `enforceable against any property which has vested in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Any licence or other instrument granted to the Company in relation to any undertaking which has`
  line `vested in the Central Government under section 3, at any time before the appointed day and in force`
  line `immediately before that day, shall continue to be in force on and after such day in accordance with its`
  line `tenor in relation to, and for the purposes of, such undertaking and on and from the day of vesting of such`
  line `undertaking under section 6 in the Cement Corporation, that Corporation shall be deemed to be`
  line `substituted in such licence or other instrument as if such licence or other instrument had been granted to`
  line `the Cement Corporation and that Corporation shall hold it for the remainder of the period for which that`
  line `Company would have held it under the terms thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) If, on the appointed day, any suit, appeal or other proceeding of wherever nature in relation to`
  line `any property which has vested in the Central Government, under section 3, instituted or preferred by or`
  line `against the Company is pending, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be, in any way,`
  line `prejudicially affected by reason of the transfer of the undertakings of the Company or of anything`
  line `contained in this Act, but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be continued, prosecuted or enforced`
  line `by or against the Central Government, or, where the undertakings of the Company are directed under`
  line `section 6 to vest in the Cement Corporation, by or against that Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (35782)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Central Government or Cement Corporation not to be liable for prior liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35782&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `liability of the Company in respect of any period prior to the appointed day, shall be the liability of the`
  line `Company and shall be enforceable against it and not against the Central Government, or, where the`
  line `undertakings of the Company are directed under section 6 to vest in the Cement Corporation, against that`
  line Corporation.
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that,--`
  line
  line `(a) save as otherwise expressly provided in this section or in any other provision of this Act, no`
  line `liability of the Company in respect of any period prior to the appointed day, shall be enforceable`
  line `against the Central Government, or where the undertakings of the Company are directed under`
  line `section 6 to vest in the Cement Corporation, against that Corporation;`
  line
  line `(b) no award, decree or order of any court, tribunal or other authority in relation to the`
  line `undertakings of the Company, passed after the appointed day, in respect of any matter, claim or`
  line `dispute which arose before that day, shall be enforceable against the Central Government, or, where`
  line `the undertakings of the Company are directed under section 6 to vest in the Cement Corporation,`
  line `against that Corporation;`
  line
  line `(c) no liability incurred by the Company before the appointed day, for the contravention of a`
  line `provision of any law for the time being in force, shall be enforceable against the Central Government,`
  line `or, where the undertakings of the Company are directed under section 6 to vest in the Cement`
  line `Corporation, against that Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (35810)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power of Central Government to direct vesting of the undertakings of the Company in Cement Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35810&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 3 and 4, the Central`
  line `Government may, subject to such terms and conditions as it may think fit to impose, direct, by`
  line `notification, that the undertakings of the Company, and the right, title and interest of the Company in`
  line `relation to its undertakings, which have vested in the Central Government under section 3, shall, instead`
  line `of continuing to vest in the Central Government, vest in the Cement Corporation either on the date of the`
  line `notification or on such earlier or later date (not being a date earlier than the appointed day) as may be`
  line `specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the right, title and interest of the Company, in relation to its undertakings, vest in the`
  line `Cement Corporation under sub-section (1), the Cement Corporation shall, on and from the date of such`
  line `vesting, be deemed to have become the owner in relation to such undertakings, and all the rights and`
  line `liabilities of the Central Government in relation to such undertakings shall, on and from the date of such`
  line `vesting, be deemed to have become the rights and liabilities of the Cement Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (35784)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Payment of amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35784&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `For the transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government, under`
  line `section 3, of the undertakings of the Company and the right, title and interest of the Company in relation`
  line `to its undertakings, there shall be paid by the central Government to the Company, in cash, and in the`
  line `manner specified in Chapter VI, an amount of rupees eighty-four lakhs and eighty-seven thousand.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (35785)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Payment of further amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35785&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The amount specified in section 7 shall carry simple interest at`
  line `the rate of four per cent. per annum for the period commencing on the appointed day and ending on the`
  line `date on which payment of such amount is made by the Central Government to the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount determined in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be paid by the`
  line `Central Government to the Company in addition to the amount specified in section 7.`
  line
  line `(3) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the liabilities of the Company in relation to its`
  line `undertakings which have vested in the Central Government under section 3, shall be discharged from the`
  line `amount referred to in section 7, and also from the amount determined under sub-section (1) in accordance`
  line `with the rights and interests of the creditors of the Company.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (35786)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Management, etc., of the undertakings of the Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2007, s. 2, for "do in relation to its undertakings" (w.e.f. 29-12-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35786&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The general superintendence,`
  line `direction, control and management of the affairs and business of the undertakings of the Company, the`
  line `right, title and interest in relation to which have vested in the Central Government under section 3, shall,`
  line `where a direction has been made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of section 6, vest in the`
  line `Cement Corporation, and thereupon the Cement Corporation shall be entitled to exercise, to the exclusion`
  line `of all other persons, all such powers and do all such things as the Company was authorised to exercise`
  line `and ^1`
  line `[do in relation to its undertakings, including the power to dispose off the assets of the undertakings`
  line `of the Company vested upon it, by the notification of the Government of India, in the Ministry of Industry`
  line `(Department of Industrial Development) number S.O. 502(E), dated the 23rd June, 1981, under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 6, if such disposal of the assets is considered necessary by the Cement`
  line `Corporation due to legal or financial considerations].`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (35811)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duty to deliver possession of the undertakings of the Company and documents relating thereto.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35811&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding any judgment, decree or order of any court, tribunal or other authority or`
  line `anything contained in any law for the time being in force, the Official Liquidator of the Company or any`
  line `other person, in whose possession or custody or under whose control the undertakings of the Company or`
  line `any part thereof may be, shall forthwith deliver possession of the undertakings of the Company or any`
  line `part thereof to the Central Government, or where the undertakings of the Company are vested under`
  line `section 6 in the Cement Corporation, to that Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) On the vesting of the management of the undertakings of the Company in the Cement`
  line `Corporation, the Official Liquidator of the Company or any other person who has, on the appointed day,`
  line `in his possession or custody or under his control any books, documents or other papers relating to the`
  line `undertakings of the Company immediately before such vesting or appointment, shall be bound to deliver`
  line `the said books, documents or other papers to the Cement Corporation or to such person as the Central`
  line `Government or the Cement Corporation, as the case may be, may specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may take or cause to be taken all necessary steps for securing possession`
  line `of the undertakings which have vested in it under section 3.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may issue such directions as it may deem desirable in the circumstances`
  line `of the case to the Cement Corporation and that Corporation may also, if it is considered necessary so to`
  line `do, apply to the Central Government at any time for instructions as to the manner in which the`
  line `management of the undertakings of the Company shall be conducted or in relation to any other matter`
  line `arising in the course of such management`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (35788)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Duty to furnish particulars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35788&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Company shall, within such period as the Central`
  line `Government may allow in this behalf, furnish to that Government or to the Cement Corporation a`
  line `complete inventory of all the properties and assets of the Company as on the appointed day pertaining to`
  line `the undertakings which have vested in the Central Government or the Cement Corporation, as the case`
  line `may be.`
  line
  line `(2) So much of the obligation of the Company, under sub-section (1) as relates to the properties and`
  line `assets of the Company in the possession, custody or control of the Official Liquidator of the Company`
  line `shall be discharged by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (35789)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Employment of certain employees to continue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35789&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who has been, immediately`
  line `before the appointed day, employed in any of the undertakings of the Company shall become,--`
  line
  line `(a) on and from the appointed day, an employee of the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the undertakings of the Company are directed under sub-section (1) of section 6, to`
  line `vest in the Cement Corporation, an employee of that Corporation on and from the date of such`
  line vesting,
  line
  line `and shall hold office or service under the Central Government or the Cement Corporation, as the case`
  line `may be, with the same rights and privileges as to pension, gratuity and other matters as would have been`
  line `admissible to him if there had been no such vesting and shall continue to do so unless and until his`
  line `employment under the Central Government or the Cement Corporation, as the case may be, is duly`
  line `terminated or until his remuneration and other conditions of service are duly altered by the Central`
  line `Government or the Cement Corporation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other person employed`
  line `in any undertaking of the Company to the Central Government or the Cement Corporation shall not`
  line `entitle such officer or other employee to any compensation under this Act or under any other law for the`
  line `time being in force and no such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority`
  line
  line `(3) Where, under the terms of any contract of service or otherwise, any person, whose services`
  line `become transferred to the Central Government or the Cement Corporation by reason of the provisions of`
  line `this Act, is entitled to any arrears of salary or wages or any payments for any leave not availed of or any`
  line `other payment, not being payment by way of gratuity or pension, such person may enforce his claim`
  line `against the Company, but not against the Central Government or the Cement Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (35790)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Provident fund and other funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35790&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Company has established a provided fund,`
  line `superannuation fund, welfare fund or any other fund for the benefit of the persons employed in any of the`
  line `undertakings of the Company, the monies relatable to the officers or other employees, whose services`
  line `have become transferred, by or under this Act, to the Central Government or the Cement Corporation,`
  line `shall, out of the monies standing, on the appointed day, to the credit of such provident fund,`
  line `superannuation fund, welfare fund or other fund, stand transferred to, and vest in, the Central Government`
  line `or the Cement Corporation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The monies which stand transferred under sub-section (1) to the Central Government or the`
  line `Cement Corporation, as the case may be, shall be dealt with by that Government or that Corporation in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (35791)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Appointment of Commissioner of Payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35791&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, for the`
  line `purpose of disbursing the amounts payable to the Company under section 7 and section 8, by notification,`
  line `appoint a Commissioner of Payments.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint such other persons as it may think fit to assist the`
  line `Commissioner and thereupon the Commissioner may authorise one or more of such persons also to`
  line `exercise all or any of the powers exercisable by him under this Act and different persons may be`
  line `authorised to exercise different powers.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person authorised by the Commissioner to exercise any of the powers exercisable by the`
  line `Commissioner may exercise those powers in the same manner and with the same effect as if they have`
  line `been conferred on that person directly by this Act and not by way of authorisation.`
  line
  line `(4) The salaries and allowances of the Commissioner and other persons appointed under this section`
  line `shall be defrayed out of the Consolidated Fund of India`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (35792)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Payment by the Central Government to the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35792&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `shall, within thirty days from the specified date, pay, in cash, to the Commissioner, for payment to the`
  line Company,--
  line
  line `(a) an amount equal to the amount specified in section 7, and`
  line
  line `(b) an amount equal to the amount payable to the Company under section 8.`
  line
  line `(2) A deposit account shall be opened by the Central Government in favour of the Commissioner in`
  line `the Public Account of India, and every amount paid under this Act to the Commissioner shall be`
  line `deposited by him to the credit of the said deposit account and the said deposit account shall be operated`
  line `by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) Records shall be maintained by the Commissioner in respect of the undertakings of the Company`
  line `in relation to which payment has been made to him under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The interest accruing on the amount standing to the credit of the deposit account referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) shall enure to the benefit of the Company`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (35793)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Certain powers of the Central Government or Cement Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35793&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government or the Cement Corporation, as the case may be, shall be entitled to receive up to the`
  line `specified date to the exclusion of all other persons, any money due to the Company, in relation to its`
  line `undertakings which have vested in the Central Government or the Cement Corporation and realised after`
  line `the appointed day, notwithstanding that the realisation pertains to a period prior to the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or the Cement Corporation, as the ease may be, may make a claim to`
  line `the Commissioner with regard to every payment made by it after the appointed day for discharging any`
  line `liability of the Company in relation to any period prior to the appointed day; and every such claim shall`
  line `have priority in accordance with the priorities attaching, under this Act, to the matter in relation to which`
  line `such liability has been discharged by the Central Government or the Cement Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the liabilities of the Company in respect of any transaction`
  line `prior to the appointed day, which have not been discharged on or before the specified date, shall be the`
  line `liabilities of the Company`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (35794)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Claims to be made to the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35794&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Every person having a claim against the Company`
  line `shall prefer such claim before the Commissioner within thirty days from the specified date:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Commissioner is satisfied that the claimant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from preferring the claim within the said period of thirty days, he may entertain the claim within a further`
  line `period of thirty days and not thereafter.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (35795)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Priority of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35795&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The claims arising out of the matters specified in the Schedule shall have`
  line `priorities in accordance with the following principles, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Category I shall have precedence over all other categories and Category II shall have`
  line `precedence over Category III, and so on;`
  line
  line `(b) the claims specified in each of the categories shall rank equally and be paid in full, but, if the`
  line `amount is insufficient to meet such claims in full, they shall abate in equal proportions and be paid`
  line `accordingly; and`
  line
  line `(c) the question of discharging any liability with regard to a matter specified in a lower category`
  line `shall arise only if a surplus is left after meeting all the liabilities specified in the immediately higher`
  line category.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (35796)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Examination of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35796&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of the claims made under section 17, the Commissioner`
  line `shall arrange the claims in the order of priorities specified in the Schedule and examine the same in`
  line `accordance with such order of priorities.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on examination of the claims, the Commissioner is of opinion that the amount paid to him`
  line `under this Act is not sufficient to meet the liabilities specified in any lower category, he shall not be`
  line `required to examine the claims in respect of such lower category.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (35797)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Admission or rejection of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35797&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) After examining the claims with reference to the`
  line `priorities set out in the Schedule, the Commissioner shall fix a certain date on or before which every`
  line `claimant shall file the proof of his claim.`
  line
  line `(2) Not less than fourteen days' notice of the date so fixed shall be given by advertisement in one`
  line `issue of any daily newspaper in the English language having circulation in the major part of the country`
  line `and one issue of any daily newspaper in such regional language as the Commissioner may consider`
  line `suitable, and every such notice shall call upon the claimant to file the proof of his claim with the`
  line `Commissioner within the period specified in the advertisement.`
  line
  line `(3) Every claimant who fails to file the proof of his claim within the time specified by the`
  line `Commissioner shall be excluded from the disbursements made by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner shall, after such investigation as may, in his opinion, be necessary and after`
  line `giving the Company an opportunity of refuting the claim and after giving the claimant a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard, by order in writing, admit or reject the claim in whole or in part.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commissioner shall have the power to regulate his own procedure in all matters arising out`
  line `of the discharge of his functions, including the place or places at which he may hold his sittings and shall,`
  line `for the purpose of making an investigation under this Act, have the same powers as are vested in a civil`
  line `court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the summoning and enforcing the attendance of any witness and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) the discovery and production of any document or other material object producible as`
  line evidence;
  line
  line `(c) the reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) the issuing of any commission for the examination of witnesses.`
  line
  line `(6) Any investigation before the Commissioner shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within`
  line `the meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Commissioner shall`
  line `be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 ( 2 of 1974 ).`
  line
  line `(7) A claimant, who is dissatisfied with the decision of the Commissioner, may prefer an appeal`
  line `against the decision to the principal civil court of original jurisdiction within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction the registered office of the Company is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a person who is a Judge of a High Court is appointed to be the Commissioner,`
  line `the appeal shall lie to the High Court of Punjab and Haryana and such appeal shall be heard and disposed`
  line `of by not less than two Judges of that High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (35798)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Disbursement of money by the Commissioner to claimants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35798&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `After admitting a claim under`
  line `this Act, the amount due in respect of such claim shall be paid by the Commissioner to the person or`
  line `persons to whom such amount is due, and, on such payment, the liability of the Company in respect of`
  line `any claim relating to the undertakings of the Company shall stand discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (35799)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Disbursement of amounts to the Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35799&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, out of the monies paid to him in relation to`
  line `the undertakings of the Company, there is a balance left after meeting the liabilities as specified in the`
  line `Schedule, the Commissioner shall disburse such balance to the Company.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the possession of any machinery, equipment or other property, has vested in the Central`
  line `Government or the Cement Corporation under this Act, but such machinery, equipment or other property`
  line `does not belong to the Company, it shall be lawful for the Central Government or the Cement Corporation`
  line `to continue to possess such machinery or equipment or other property on the same terms and conditions`
  line `under which it was possessed by the Company immediately before the appointed day`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (35800)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Undisbursed or unclaimed amount to be deposited to the general revenue account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35800&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `money paid to the Commissioner which remains undisbursed or unclaimed on the date immediately`
  line `preceding the date on which the office of the Commissioner is finally wound up, shall be transferred by`
  line `the Commissioner, before his office is finally wound up, to the general revenue account of the Central`
  line `Government; but a claim to any money so transferred may be preferred to the Central Government by the`
  line `person entitled to such payment and shall be dealt with as if such transfer had not been made, and the`
  line `order, in any, for payment of the claim, being treated as an order for the refund of revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (35801)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35801&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law, other than this Act, or in any decree or order of any court, tribunal or`
  line `other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (35812)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Contracts to cease to have effect unless ratified by Central Government or Cement Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35812&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Every contract entered into by the Company in relation to its undertakings, which has`
  line `vested in the Central Government under section 3, for any service, sale or supply and in force`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, shall, on and from the expiry of one hundred and eighty days from`
  line `the appointed day, cease to have effect unless such contract is, before the expiry of that period, ratified, in`
  line `writing, by the Central Government or the Cement Corporation, where such undertakings have been`
  line `vested in that Corporation under this Act, and in ratifying such contract, the Central Government or the`
  line `Cement Corporation may make such alteration or modification therein as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government or the Cement Corporation shall not omit to ratify contract and`
  line `shall not make any alteration or modification in a contract--`
  line
  line `(a) unless it is satisfied that such contract is unduly onerous or has been entered into in bad faith`
  line `or is detrimental to the interests of the Central Government or the Cement Corporation, and`
  line
  line `(b) except after giving to the parties to the contract a reasonable opportunity of being heard and`
  line `except after recording in writing its reasons for refusal to ratify the contract or for making any`
  line `alteration or modification therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (35803)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35803&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or any officer or other employee of that Government or the`
  line `Cement Corporation or other person authorised by that Government or Corporation for anything which is`
  line `in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or any officer or other`
  line `employee of that Government or the Cement Corporation or other person authorised by that Government`
  line `or Corporation for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (35804)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Delegation of Powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35804&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, direct that all or any`
  line `of the powers exercisable by it under this Act, other than the powers conferred by this section, section 30`
  line `and section 31, may also be exercised by such person or persons as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any delegation of power is made under sub-section (1), the person to whom such power`
  line `has been delegated shall act under the direction, control and supervision of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (35805)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35805&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) having in his possession, custody or control any property forming part of any undertakings of`
  line `the Company, wrongfully withholds such property from the Central Government or the Cement`
  line `Corporation; or`
  line
  line `(b) wrongfully obtains possession of, or retains, any property forming part of, the undertakings of`
  line `the Company; or`
  line
  line `(c) wilfully withholds or fails to furnish to the Central Government or the Cement Corporation or`
  line `to any person or body of persons specified by that Government or the Cement Corporation, as the`
  line `case may be, any document or inventory relating to the undertakings of the Company, which may be`
  line `in his possession, custody or control; or`
  line
  line `(d) fails to deliver to the Central Government or the Cement Corporation or to any person or body`
  line `of persons specified by that Government or the Cement Corporation, any assets, books of account,`
  line `registers or other documents in his possession, custody or control relating to the undertakings of the`
  line `Company;, or`
  line
  line `(e) wrongfully removes or destroys any property forming part of the undertakings of the`
  line `Company; or`
  line
  line `(f) prefers any claim under this Act which he knows or has reasonable cause to believe to be false`
  line `or grossly inaccurate,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (35806)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35806&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company, for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company,`
  line `shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (35807)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35807&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the time within which, and the manner in which, an intimation shall be given to the`
  line `Commissioner under sub-section (3) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which the monies in any provident fund or other fund under section 13 shall be`
  line `dealt with;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is required to be, or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (35808)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35808&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the appointed`
  line day
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (35809)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377&sectionId=35809&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_000010_198131_1517807325377
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Dalmia Dadri Cement Limited (Acquisition and Transfer of`
  line `Undertakings) Ordinance, 1981 (6 of 1981), is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
